

URL = http://text.totalism.org/

=Description=

"Text.Totalism is an attempt to establish a software platform & also the
content of a hypertextual compendium of theory ("TTarchive"), featuring F2F
spread and content access, ability to latently reference any piece of any
written text ("LinkRoute"), and most of all, the study of novel, advanced
forms of dealing with theory ("HyperReader"): annotation, textual layers,
"every read is an interpretation is a theoretical addition", Remix,
co&juxta-positioning of versions, etc. 

At the same time, the whole logic of
choice ("what to read") is also considered and made a part of the system,
denying legitimacy to arbitrary pickings in libraries/bookshops, and
actively referring to the next of your 1000 books you'll ever read (out of
the ~100 mil.). An alternative is investigated and programatically put in
place to the known institutions of university reading lists, chasing
references in likeable texts, and showers of recomendations.

We are in contact with OKFN's Textus/OpenPhilosophy project."
(http://text.totalism.org/whatis.txt)

